      {
        "id": "75178c2fff520a231d1fc781f53dd093db507fde",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 189,
          "name": "HuabingZhao",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "huabingzhao@tencent.com",
          "username": "HuabingZhao"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-10-10 07:17:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Kanagaraj, as we agreed in Paris F2F, let's using CLI to register services in a separated script and it can be an alternative way for service registration after testing.\nCurrently, it's an urgent issue, I prefer we quickly fix it so we can move on to the integration test.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "b559627a3277e65c74cf7ba0e7824cd251e24db9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 741,
          "name": "Kanagaraj Manickam",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "kanagaraj.manickam@huawei.com",
          "username": "mkr1481"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-10-10 07:43:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Huabing, path and enable_ssl was required only for certain set of the services and CLI could be fixed for them in 2 mins. and please file bug on cli, in case if you find any such issue in future. thanks.\n\nI have one question. while i saw the changes made in this commit, only 11 services are registered with path and path is same as url value. so please let me know why user should provide both path and url with same value ?\n\nthank you.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "6770a2e8c61e0c6d055e127c3da79da5be52c19b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 189,
          "name": "HuabingZhao",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "huabingzhao@tencent.com",
          "username": "HuabingZhao"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-10-10 07:55:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Kanagaraj,\nI believe you can fix them soon. But it might have other issues as well and I don't want to block the integration test. We could do it in parallel. After the CLI version is verified, we can use it for service registration.\n\nThis commit itself has no issue, so please +1 so it can be submitted.\n\nFor the usage of path, it's the customized publish path of the registered service.If path parameter is specified when registering the service, the service will be published to apigateway under this path. Otherwise, the service will be published to apigateway using a fixed format: api/{serviceName}/{version}. The customized publish path should only be used for back-compatible.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "921448cf109064617ea8a1a32ab1a2b16b413cb1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 741,
          "name": "Kanagaraj Manickam",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "kanagaraj.manickam@huawei.com",
          "username": "mkr1481"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-10-10 08:10:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review\n\nRemoving my -1, as ESR is blocked and looking for the change immediately. i will land the fix for CLI asap.\n\nif you have time, i would suggested to make changes only for those service requires path and enable_ssl instead of changing all entries.\n\nThanks.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
